About Us - History

Timeline

1978

Establishment of Our Club

In 1978, our club was founded in Hong Kong by several famous distance runners, including Graham Smith, Tam Wai Man (譚偉文). Many elite distance runners joined our club: marathon runners Yu Kuai Hung (余桂雄) and Chik Ho Shing (植浩星), as well as Cheung Chi Wah (張志華), Hung Hing Keung (孔慶強), Chan Chi Yan (陳志仁), Lee Ho Tung (李浩東), etc.

mid-80s

Rapid Expansion of Our Club

The number of club members soared in the mid-80s as more and more youth athletes and experienced runners joined us.

1989

Champion - Hong Kong Cross Country Championships (Open)

With numerous elite club members, our club outshined other clubs and won the Hong Kong Cross-Country Championships in the open category. This was our first victory in the events.


1990s

Focus on Youth Athletes Training

In this period, we cultivated multiple elite youth athletes, such as Gi Ka Man (紀嘉文), Chan Ka Ho (陳家豪), Lau Tak Lung (劉德龍), Chan Ka Wai (陳嘉威) and so on. 

2004

Champion - Hong Kong Cross Country Championships (Open & Youth)

Fifteen years after the first champion in 1989, we achieved a victory in Hong Kong Cross Country Championships in both open and youth categories.

About
無論是健體、享樂或挑戰自己都以快樂地跑為目標。以跑會友，擴闊社交圈子。
本會提供成人及小朋友訓練課程

課程介紹:
星期一, 成人享樂健體班
星期三, 成績進階班
星期五, 少年短跑班
星期日, 晨早健體長課班

Mission
專業正確訓練方法 , 回饋社會!
1. 為喜愛跑步的大小朋友提供專業技術的教授
2. 科學化的訓練法
3. 快樂享受跑步樂趣

From the old website: 推動長跑運動，透過刻苦的訓練及比賽，建立團隊精神、健康及豐盛的人生。
